01:00.862 --> 01:03.517
- Mikey, next time,
I would appreciate a heads-up.

01:03.586 --> 01:06.517
- Okay.
Heads up!

01:06.586 --> 01:07.620
Is that...

01:07.689 --> 01:09.862
- [gasps] It is!

01:09.931 --> 01:12.655
The Jupiter Jim Moon Buggy!

01:12.724 --> 01:14.827
Featured in not one,
not two,

01:14.896 --> 01:16.379
but 60 sequels

01:16.448 --> 01:18.862
of "Jupiter Jim's
Last Trip to the Moon."

01:18.931 --> 01:20.344
Ah!

01:23.586 --> 01:25.793
- How could anybody let
that historical gem

01:25.862 --> 01:27.000
slip through their fingers?

01:27.068 --> 01:28.620
- I do not know, Michael,

01:28.689 --> 01:29.931
but we've got to have it.

01:30.000 --> 01:32.931
[stealthy music]

01:33.000 --> 01:34.793
♪ ♪

01:34.862 --> 01:36.793
- But how are we gonna
get the car?

01:36.862 --> 01:39.758
We can't go and talk
to one of those human people.

01:39.827 --> 01:41.862
[loud crash]

01:41.931 --> 01:44.241
[rock music]

01:44.310 --> 01:46.034
- Who the heck are youse?

01:46.103 --> 01:47.275
- Oh, no, a mutant!

01:47.344 --> 01:49.793
Wait, we're mutants too.
It's okay.

01:49.862 --> 01:51.758
- Dude, you better hide.

01:51.827 --> 01:54.034
There's a human guy
around here.

01:54.103 --> 01:57.034
- Easy, easy.

01:57.103 --> 01:58.931
This is Repo Mantis Salvage.

01:59.000 --> 02:00.758
The guy is me.

02:00.827 --> 02:03.034
- This is your lot?

02:03.103 --> 02:04.620
You have to sell us
that moon buggy!

02:04.689 --> 02:05.827
Please!
Ah!

02:05.896 --> 02:07.275
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

02:07.344 --> 02:08.931
Cool your scramjets, buddy.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.724
This is a negotiation.

02:11.793 --> 02:13.758
We gotta play it smooth.

02:13.827 --> 02:16.758
[bold percussive music]

02:16.827 --> 02:23.000
♪ ♪

02:23.068 --> 02:24.896
- So, uh, how much
you gonna pay us

02:24.965 --> 02:27.620
to take this pile of parts
off your hands, amigo?

02:27.689 --> 02:28.724
- Scram.

02:28.793 --> 02:31.206
I got a lot of fenders
to count.

02:31.275 --> 02:33.655
- I see you drive
a hard bargain, sir.

02:33.724 --> 02:35.482
Well, perhaps
I can interest you

02:35.551 --> 02:37.000
in a little coin.

02:37.068 --> 02:39.137
I've got big silver,
small silver,

02:39.206 --> 02:41.206
and I can make it rain
copper, daddy.

02:41.275 --> 02:43.965
[underwhelming musical tones]

02:44.034 --> 02:46.068
[dramatic musical tone]

02:46.137 --> 02:49.310
- Hey, you ain't got
nearly enough, but say,

02:49.379 --> 02:52.103
I could use a couple
of tough muties like you.

02:52.172 --> 02:55.137
Ever do any repo work?

02:55.206 --> 02:56.896
- Of course!

02:56.965 --> 02:58.827
No.
What's repo work?

02:58.896 --> 03:00.482
- It's when you take stuff back

03:00.551 --> 03:03.172
from deadbeats
who didn't pay for it.

03:03.241 --> 03:04.655
Do a job for me today,

03:04.724 --> 03:07.310
and I'll let you have
that moon buggy thing.

03:07.379 --> 03:09.413
- We're in.
- And...sidebar.

03:09.482 --> 03:12.241
Look, Mikey, repo men
have to be mean,

03:12.310 --> 03:13.413
and I don't know
if you know this,

03:13.482 --> 03:14.551
but you're kind of a softie.

03:14.620 --> 03:16.827
- That really hurts
my feelings!

03:16.896 --> 03:17.965
Oh.

03:18.034 --> 03:18.965
You have a point.

03:19.034 --> 03:20.241
But I can do this.

03:20.310 --> 03:22.620
Hard as nails.
Grr.

03:22.689 --> 03:23.551
We're in.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.172
What's the skinny, chico?

03:25.241 --> 03:27.172
- I need you to get an RV

03:27.241 --> 03:29.068
from a real shady mutant.

03:29.137 --> 03:30.482
Holes up in the woods

03:30.551 --> 03:32.482
on the wrong side
of the tracks,

03:32.551 --> 03:36.689
in the darkest outskirts
of the bad part of town.

03:36.758 --> 03:39.275
- Thanks for the ride!
Ah!

03:39.344 --> 03:41.172
- I ran a profile on this guy.

03:41.241 --> 03:43.068
Lawless loner,
doesn't pay his bills,

03:43.137 --> 03:45.586
lives in this
very spooky forest.

03:45.655 --> 03:48.724
He is a 98% match
for the Spine-Breaking Bandit!

03:48.793 --> 03:51.413
[dramatic music]

03:51.482 --> 03:52.482
- Pfft.
I'm not scared

03:52.551 --> 03:54.655
of some no-good forest dweller!

03:54.724 --> 03:56.068
Let's see him!

03:56.137 --> 03:58.172
There's his RV!

03:58.241 --> 04:01.068
[growling noises]

04:01.137 --> 04:02.551
both: Ah!

04:02.620 --> 04:04.068
- That's the biggest
forest dweller

04:04.137 --> 04:05.379
I've ever seen!
- He is totally

04:05.448 --> 04:06.758
gonna break our spines.

04:06.827 --> 04:08.344
Maybe we should call
Raph and Leo.

04:08.413 --> 04:10.655
- No, no, no, no, no!
We got this.

04:10.724 --> 04:12.241
Think of all the boss
adventures

04:12.310 --> 04:13.931
we could have in
the moon buggy!

04:14.000 --> 04:15.517
- Ah, all right.

04:15.586 --> 04:16.965
If you are dead-set
on doing this,

04:17.034 --> 04:18.724
we gotta go stealth.

04:18.793 --> 04:20.241
Sneak-jitsu 101:

04:20.310 --> 04:22.896
Never let a spine-breaker
get behind you.

04:22.965 --> 04:25.517
[both scream]
- No! He's behind us!

04:25.586 --> 04:27.689
He is directly behind us!

04:27.758 --> 04:29.344
Ah!

04:29.413 --> 04:30.620
Ah!
- Oof!

04:30.689 --> 04:31.724
Ah.

04:31.793 --> 04:35.172
[dramatic music]

04:35.241 --> 04:36.551
- Hey, I'm Todd!

04:36.620 --> 04:38.344
Welcome to Cuddle Cakes
Puppy Rescue,

04:38.413 --> 04:40.689
the puppy-est place on earth!

04:40.758 --> 04:42.241
[laughs]

04:42.310 --> 04:43.827
- Puppies.

04:43.896 --> 04:45.241
Right.

04:45.310 --> 04:47.517
And which one are you having
for dinner?

04:47.586 --> 04:51.413
- Oh, right!
It's dinner time!

04:52.344 --> 04:55.551
[jaunty music]

04:58.275 --> 04:59.551
Hey, you guys want some of my

04:59.620 --> 05:01.758
Internet-famous
homemade lemonade?

05:01.827 --> 05:06.034
I donate it to folks in Alaska
who need a little sunshine.

05:06.103 --> 05:09.000
[gentle music]

05:09.068 --> 05:10.482
- Oh, wow.
This is pretty good.

05:10.551 --> 05:13.103
- That honestly tastes
exactly like sunshine.

05:13.172 --> 05:15.310
Wow.
And sidebar.

05:15.379 --> 05:18.862
Cute puppies,
nonprofit lemonade?

05:18.931 --> 05:20.482
This is no
spine-breaking bandit.

05:20.551 --> 05:22.482
- He's the nicest guy
in the world.

05:22.551 --> 05:24.413
- But we need that RV.

05:24.482 --> 05:26.793
We gotta be tough with him.

05:26.862 --> 05:27.793
Hard as nails!

05:27.862 --> 05:29.862
[extended slurping]

05:29.931 --> 05:31.758
- Got it.

05:31.827 --> 05:33.689
[dramatic music]

05:33.758 --> 05:35.620
So, Todd,

05:35.689 --> 05:38.310
let's get down to business
about your RV.

05:38.379 --> 05:40.379
- Sure thing!

05:40.448 --> 05:41.724
Could you hold Willis?

05:41.793 --> 05:45.103
- Oh, I d--I don't know
if I'm--no!

05:45.172 --> 05:47.827
Aww, you little mischief-maker!

05:47.896 --> 05:49.965
Wait a minute.
We're supposed to be talking

05:50.034 --> 05:51.000
about your RV.

05:51.068 --> 05:52.275
- Look, Todd.

05:52.344 --> 05:54.517
You haven't made a payment
in two years,

05:54.586 --> 05:55.965
and that means--
- Yeah.

05:56.034 --> 05:58.413
Turns out, all you get
for rescuing puppies

05:58.482 --> 05:59.931
are million-dollar smiles.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.241
[puppy barks]

06:01.310 --> 06:03.000
Ooh, Miho wants
her belly rubbed.

06:03.068 --> 06:06.000
- My hard-as-nails brother
and I are here to--

06:06.068 --> 06:09.275
- And I'll call you
Indiana Bones,

06:09.344 --> 06:11.137
and you Little Bones.

06:11.206 --> 06:12.586
- Mikey, come on!

06:12.655 --> 06:13.689
Oh!

06:13.758 --> 06:15.758
- [laughs] Melvin wants
to play!

06:15.827 --> 06:17.689
Could you toss his ball?
- Okay, fine.

06:17.758 --> 06:20.931
I will toss the ball if you
give us the keys to your--

06:21.000 --> 06:23.689
I am in something squishy.
I am in something squishy!

06:23.758 --> 06:26.103
- Oh, yeah, I am so swamped,

06:26.172 --> 06:27.862
I never get
to clean the yard up.

06:27.931 --> 06:31.000
But you guys
are so good at this!

06:31.068 --> 06:33.068
Do you want to grab
a couple shovels?

06:34.275 --> 06:36.931
[Mikey and Donnie grunting]

06:37.000 --> 06:38.551
- [sighs]

06:38.620 --> 06:40.413
Why did we just do that?

06:40.482 --> 06:42.068
- I don't know, Michael.

06:42.137 --> 06:43.482
I don't know.

06:43.551 --> 06:45.551
Niceness is his superpower!

06:45.620 --> 06:48.551
- Ah, you guys
must be exhausted.

06:48.620 --> 06:50.172
Why don't you sleep over?

06:50.241 --> 06:52.379
In the morning,
I can hold Sir Chomps-A-Lot

06:52.448 --> 06:54.413
while you guys floss
his giant fangs!

06:54.482 --> 06:56.655
- That sounds gr--
no, no.

06:56.724 --> 06:58.241
We didn't come here
to help you.

06:58.310 --> 07:00.137
We came here
to repo your RV.

07:00.206 --> 07:01.724
- Okay.

07:01.793 --> 07:03.034
Yeah, I guess me and the pups

07:03.103 --> 07:05.413
will just sleep under the stars
tonight.

07:05.482 --> 07:07.241
[distant thunder]

07:07.310 --> 07:08.310
[sniffing]

07:08.379 --> 07:11.310
[morose music]

07:11.379 --> 07:12.862
♪ ♪

07:12.931 --> 07:14.551
And every night,

07:14.620 --> 07:18.379
through puppy hurricane season!

07:18.448 --> 07:20.551
[cries]

07:20.620 --> 07:23.448
♪ ♪

07:23.517 --> 07:26.448
- I can't do it!

07:26.517 --> 07:28.482
- Okay, Todd.

07:28.551 --> 07:29.965
[clears throat]

07:30.034 --> 07:33.517
How about you trade us
that dusty RV,

07:33.586 --> 07:37.586
and we make you
a new place to sleep, huh?

07:37.655 --> 07:40.689
- [gasps] Really?

07:40.758 --> 07:42.413
And a place to feed
the puppies,

07:42.482 --> 07:45.758
and bathe and diaper
and play with them?

07:45.827 --> 07:48.103
- Yes.
- I don't suppose that--

07:48.172 --> 07:50.931
- Yes, obviously, there will be
robot assistants!

07:52.000 --> 07:53.206
- And go!

07:53.275 --> 07:56.206
[upbeat rock music]

07:56.275 --> 08:03.551
♪ ♪

08:27.551 --> 08:30.931
Thanks, guys!
I'll never forget you!

08:31.000 --> 08:32.344
And come back

08:32.413 --> 08:34.517
if you ever want
to milk the puppies!

08:34.586 --> 08:38.068
They have eight nipples!
- No, stop! No.

08:38.137 --> 08:39.551
both: Hard as nails!

08:39.620 --> 08:42.310
- All right!
- We did it!

08:42.379 --> 08:44.620
Hey, Repo!

08:44.689 --> 08:46.379
One RV, as promised.

08:46.448 --> 08:48.413
Wax up that moon buggy, baby.

08:48.482 --> 08:50.724
- Not bad, not bad.

08:50.793 --> 08:52.379
But what had happened was...

08:52.448 --> 08:54.206
I ain't giving it to you.

08:54.275 --> 08:55.241
Turns out,

08:55.310 --> 08:56.620
dorky Jupiter Jim fans'll

08:56.689 --> 08:58.517
pay big bucks just to sit
in that thing!

08:58.586 --> 09:00.689
- What?
We had a deal, buddy-o.

09:00.758 --> 09:03.068
- Scrapping is
a tricky business, kids,

09:03.137 --> 09:04.379
and you got tricked.

09:04.448 --> 09:06.103
- We are not leaving

09:06.172 --> 09:07.379
without our moon buggy.

09:07.448 --> 09:09.413
- Hey, the purple one's funny!

09:09.482 --> 09:10.862
- I keep telling you guys
I'm funny.

09:10.931 --> 09:13.137
- I'm gonna break your legs

09:13.206 --> 09:15.793
halfway through...twice.

09:15.862 --> 09:16.586
Ah!

09:16.655 --> 09:17.620
- Ha!

09:17.689 --> 09:19.034
Mikey, the magnet!

09:19.103 --> 09:20.379
- Hmm?

09:20.448 --> 09:23.379
[rock music]

09:23.448 --> 09:26.103
♪ ♪

09:26.172 --> 09:28.793
- [sputtering]
- A deal's a deal, chico!

09:28.862 --> 09:31.034
- Is there anything
magnets can't do?

09:31.103 --> 09:33.241
- Ah!
Ooh!

09:33.310 --> 09:36.448
[giddy laughter]

09:36.517 --> 09:37.758
Tallyho!

09:37.827 --> 09:40.137
- Eat crater dust, bug man!

09:40.206 --> 09:42.344
- [panting]

09:42.413 --> 09:45.931
[grunts]

09:46.000 --> 09:47.448
[chuckles]

09:47.517 --> 09:49.724
[horn sounds]

09:49.793 --> 09:51.689
- Man, this thing
is super slow.

09:51.758 --> 09:53.103
- Of course it is.

09:53.172 --> 09:56.103
It was built for the gravity
of the Moon.

09:56.172 --> 09:59.310
- Give me back
my dork-mobile!

09:59.379 --> 10:01.862
- Moon-core lasers, activate!

10:01.931 --> 10:03.206
Oh...
- Uh...

10:03.275 --> 10:04.620
- Crater dust cloud...

10:04.689 --> 10:05.965
- Should that do anything?

10:06.034 --> 10:08.068
- Zero-atmosphere
Gatling missiles?

10:08.137 --> 10:09.103
Ah, nuts.

10:09.172 --> 10:10.206
[both yell]

10:10.275 --> 10:12.344
- [laughs maniacally]

10:12.413 --> 10:14.000
[rock music]

10:14.068 --> 10:15.896
- This is a movie vehicle, pal.

10:15.965 --> 10:18.310
They wouldn't load it up
with advanced lunar artillery.

10:18.379 --> 10:19.896
- Not unless
it's the moon buggy

10:19.965 --> 10:22.482
from "Jupiter Jim's
Third Last Trip to the moon,"

10:22.551 --> 10:23.827
which had a fake dashboard

10:23.896 --> 10:25.620
to fool the Plutonians!

10:25.689 --> 10:27.034
Pasta fazool!

10:27.103 --> 10:30.551
I'm kicking in Jupiter Jim
Titan Turbo Mode!

10:30.620 --> 10:32.551
[both cheering]

10:32.620 --> 10:35.586
- [growls]

10:35.655 --> 10:40.034
♪ ♪

10:40.103 --> 10:41.137
- I can't shake him.

10:41.206 --> 10:44.206
- I'll try
the Gravity Grease 3000.

10:44.275 --> 10:45.413
Crowd: Oil! Ah, oil!

10:45.482 --> 10:47.793
Oil?
This is gonna...

10:47.862 --> 10:49.551
- I think we got
a bunch of people

10:49.620 --> 10:51.034
pretty oily.
Ow!

10:51.103 --> 10:53.896
[horn honking]

10:53.965 --> 10:55.586
- Maybe the bug-zapper button.
- Really?

10:55.655 --> 10:58.758
There is a bug-zapper but--
why didn't you try that first?

10:58.827 --> 11:01.827
- It didn't have
a 3000 after it.

11:01.896 --> 11:03.172
- There. Happy?

11:03.241 --> 11:04.896
- Why, thank you.

11:04.965 --> 11:07.206
[electronic humming]

11:07.275 --> 11:09.344
- Oh...

11:09.413 --> 11:11.896
What a pretty tone of blue.

11:11.965 --> 11:14.344
Ow!

11:14.413 --> 11:16.448
[spacey electronic music]

11:16.517 --> 11:18.137
both: Hard as nails!

11:18.206 --> 11:20.931
♪ ♪

11:21.000 --> 11:22.620
- [laughs]
Those guys.

11:25.379 --> 11:27.758
[thumping techno music
playing]

11:27.827 --> 11:29.793
- Yeah, all right.

11:29.862 --> 11:31.068
- Get 'em.

11:31.137 --> 11:32.034
- [grunting]

11:32.103 --> 11:33.620
- I don't think
he's got this.

11:33.689 --> 11:35.586
- Hey! Leave him alone.

11:35.655 --> 11:37.517
- What? I'm just saying
he doesn't have this.

11:37.586 --> 11:38.931
- You're just trying
to get in my head.

11:39.000 --> 11:42.137
- Oh, my peaches and cream,
he just doubled.

11:42.206 --> 11:45.448
- [coughing and wheezing]

11:45.517 --> 11:47.344
- Rag! Now!

11:47.413 --> 11:50.344
- Have I ever told you
how big and beautiful you are?

11:50.413 --> 11:51.862
- No, but thank you.

11:51.931 --> 11:53.827
- Uh, he is about to set
a new high score.

11:53.896 --> 11:56.413
I can't watch,
but I can't not watch!

11:56.482 --> 11:58.068
- [coughing]

11:58.137 --> 12:03.551
[labored breathing]

12:03.620 --> 12:05.724
♪ ♪

12:05.793 --> 12:08.034
- You know what they say
about big-time moments?

12:08.103 --> 12:09.068
- Yes, I do.

12:09.137 --> 12:10.448
They say that in big-time
moments,

12:10.517 --> 12:11.448
leaders make--

12:11.517 --> 12:14.379
- Brain!

12:14.448 --> 12:17.034
- Game over.

12:17.103 --> 12:19.206
- Ow, my brain!

12:19.275 --> 12:20.931
- No!

12:21.000 --> 12:21.724
Why?

12:21.793 --> 12:23.655
- [inhales heavily]

12:23.724 --> 12:25.206
[sneezes weakly]

12:25.275 --> 12:26.620
- Gesundheit.

12:26.689 --> 12:29.137
- Omigosh, omigosh, omigosh,
Splinter's a zombie!

12:29.206 --> 12:32.448
- Mikey, zombies are interested
in other people's brains.

12:32.517 --> 12:34.655
- Rat Flu.
This is not a drill.

12:34.724 --> 12:37.793
I repeat,
this is not a drill, boys.

12:40.586 --> 12:42.379
- I feel terrible.

12:42.448 --> 12:43.586
Do I look terrible?

12:43.655 --> 12:45.344
Be honest.

12:45.413 --> 12:47.482
[woman screams]

12:47.551 --> 12:49.620
- Whoa!
- Okay.

12:49.689 --> 12:52.758
- You look great,
not horribly sick at all.

12:52.827 --> 12:54.758
He's horribly sick.

12:54.827 --> 12:56.241
- Look, a flu this intense

12:56.310 --> 12:58.137
is going to affect
all areas of his brain--

12:58.206 --> 13:01.758
I'm talking
the full seven stages--

13:01.827 --> 13:03.862
before his body
naturally heals itself.

13:03.931 --> 13:06.310
- You guys know what
the full seven stages mean?

13:06.379 --> 13:07.758
- Mm-hmm.

13:07.827 --> 13:11.000
- Another chance to get
whatever we want!

13:11.068 --> 13:12.551
all: Yeah!

13:12.620 --> 13:14.517
- But poor Dad.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.310
He must feel terrible.

13:16.379 --> 13:20.137
But lucky us, he'll say yes
to whatever we ask for!

13:20.206 --> 13:21.517
Whoo-hoo!

13:21.586 --> 13:25.310
- Only if we make it all
the way to end of the flu,

13:25.379 --> 13:28.655
the elusive
stage seven.

13:28.724 --> 13:30.448
And we never get there.

13:30.517 --> 13:32.413
- This year's gonna be
different.

13:32.482 --> 13:33.862
Nobody's getting bit.

13:33.931 --> 13:35.413
Nobody's getting infected.

13:35.482 --> 13:36.793
- When we do
make it to the end,

13:36.862 --> 13:39.586
which I'm now calling
the Must Say Yes stage,

13:39.655 --> 13:41.551
what are we gonna ask for?

13:41.620 --> 13:43.241
all: Hmm...

13:43.310 --> 13:44.724
- Hmm.

13:44.793 --> 13:47.413
Well, this year, I was
thinking we could ask for,

13:47.482 --> 13:49.034
uh, um, er--uh...

13:49.103 --> 13:50.724
- Aww, he's got nothing.
We're dead.

13:50.793 --> 13:52.310
- Hey, I got something,
all right?

13:52.379 --> 13:53.310
Like a, uh--

13:53.379 --> 13:54.586
- Uranium!

13:54.655 --> 13:57.344
Oh, we should absolutely
ask for uranium.

13:57.413 --> 13:59.206
I mean, if I could finally
get my hands

13:59.275 --> 14:01.793
on a little of that, we would
be virtually unstoppa--

14:01.862 --> 14:03.586
- What about a brick oven
for pizza?

14:03.655 --> 14:05.206
- Who's gonna clean that?

14:05.275 --> 14:08.137
What we should ask for
is matching unicorn onesies.

14:08.206 --> 14:10.793
Those are sick! Pun intended.

14:10.862 --> 14:12.241
And I nailed it.

14:12.310 --> 14:13.379
[all grunting]

14:13.448 --> 14:15.586
- Enough.
I got this, all right?

14:15.655 --> 14:16.896
I'm gonna ask Splinter

14:16.965 --> 14:18.448
for something
that benefits all of us.

14:18.517 --> 14:20.517
- This is so exciting!

14:20.586 --> 14:22.482
But terrible for Dad.

14:22.551 --> 14:25.551
[gasps]

14:26.482 --> 14:30.068
- Buckle up, boys.
It's about to get weird.

14:33.310 --> 14:34.482
[air whooshing]

14:34.551 --> 14:37.827
- [babbling]

14:37.896 --> 14:39.379
[razor buzzing]

14:39.448 --> 14:41.793
[all shivering]

14:41.862 --> 14:43.448
- I hate stage one.

14:43.517 --> 14:44.655
Think warm
thoughts.

14:44.724 --> 14:47.241
Pizza ovens.
Bricks from Italy.

14:47.310 --> 14:49.034
Wood chips roasting.

14:49.103 --> 14:50.517
- We're four hours in.

14:50.586 --> 14:52.758
His fever's
gotta break soon.

14:52.827 --> 14:55.068
- I told you guys
to plan ahead.

14:55.137 --> 14:57.172
Now I'm sitting here
all toasty.

14:57.241 --> 14:58.517
[slurps]

14:58.586 --> 14:59.586
[spits]

14:59.655 --> 15:01.689
What? Wha--
Why?

15:01.758 --> 15:07.000
- Had to air myself out.

15:09.344 --> 15:10.758
[growls]

15:10.827 --> 15:11.793
[screeches]

15:11.862 --> 15:14.172
[all screaming]

15:17.000 --> 15:19.310
[all screaming]

15:19.379 --> 15:20.379
- Don't eat me!

15:20.448 --> 15:21.931
Raph's tastier!

15:22.000 --> 15:23.034
- Suits on! Suits on!

15:23.103 --> 15:24.241
Donnie, get the device ready.

15:24.310 --> 15:25.724
- Uh, it's ready.

15:25.793 --> 15:28.586
You know, my inspiration
for this device was simplicity.

15:28.655 --> 15:31.241
Why dress something up
with lots of bells and whistles

15:31.310 --> 15:32.724
when you can just let it
speak for its--

15:32.793 --> 15:35.482
- No one has time for this!

15:35.551 --> 15:38.620
[deep rumbling]

15:38.689 --> 15:41.413
[grunts]

15:41.482 --> 15:42.793
- Nice!

15:42.862 --> 15:45.275
All right,
let's get him inside.

15:45.344 --> 15:48.137
- [snarling]

15:50.620 --> 15:52.793
- Okay, this should hold him
for a while.

15:52.862 --> 15:54.241
- And you're sure
this isn't cruel?

15:54.310 --> 15:55.620
- He loves pizza

15:55.689 --> 15:57.655
and confined spaces
you can barely breathe in.

15:57.724 --> 15:59.793
- Donnie, is it gonna hold up?

15:59.862 --> 16:02.413
- Most definitely!

16:02.482 --> 16:03.965
- [snarling]

16:04.034 --> 16:07.689
- [screaming]

16:07.758 --> 16:10.689
[hard rock music]

16:10.758 --> 16:13.379
♪ ♪

16:13.448 --> 16:15.310
- [snarling]

16:15.379 --> 16:16.413
- Aah!

16:16.482 --> 16:18.379
- Mikey, follow me,
and be careful.

16:18.448 --> 16:21.896
We can't afford to lose anyone
before stage seven.

16:21.965 --> 16:23.275
- I thought we all agreed

16:23.344 --> 16:26.448
it was now called
the Must Say Yes stage.

16:26.517 --> 16:28.965
- It would be easier for me
to be careful

16:29.034 --> 16:31.965
if I knew you were gonna
ask for a pizza oven.

16:32.034 --> 16:33.482
- I'm still thinking!

16:33.551 --> 16:35.655
- Quick question:
is uranium still on the table?

16:35.724 --> 16:37.068
- Ugh!

16:39.068 --> 16:42.000
Where's Splinter?
Mikey, you smell him?

16:42.068 --> 16:45.000
[suspenseful music]

16:45.068 --> 16:46.586
♪ ♪

16:46.655 --> 16:48.655
- [whimpers]

16:48.724 --> 16:52.275
♪ ♪

16:52.344 --> 16:53.620
[gasps]

16:53.689 --> 16:56.103
- [sighs]
- [gasping]

16:56.172 --> 16:57.275
- He's not under there.

16:57.344 --> 16:58.241
- Uh...

16:58.310 --> 17:00.103
- What?
- [shrieks]

17:00.172 --> 17:02.344
- Use your words.

17:02.413 --> 17:05.000
- He's...on...you.

17:05.068 --> 17:07.793
- What? Heats on stew?

17:07.862 --> 17:09.896
- He's on you.

17:09.965 --> 17:10.896
- He's on me?

17:10.965 --> 17:12.068
- Yes.

17:12.137 --> 17:15.241
- [snarls]
- [screams]

17:16.379 --> 17:18.793
- [snarling]

17:18.862 --> 17:21.965
Oh, my favorite son.

17:22.034 --> 17:24.310
- Favorite son? Run!

17:28.103 --> 17:30.862
- Ugh, these things
do not breathe.

17:30.931 --> 17:32.137
- I know, right?

17:32.206 --> 17:33.965
Uh, now, are we sure
we're safe?

17:34.034 --> 17:35.896
- Calm down.
We're fine.

17:35.965 --> 17:37.862
Raph and Mikey have it
under contr--oh, no.

17:37.931 --> 17:39.275
- Stage three. Stage three.

17:39.344 --> 17:42.758
- Oh, little baby blue,
come to Papa.

17:42.827 --> 17:45.793
- Suits on! Suits on!

17:45.862 --> 17:46.931
- Why weren't you
in your suits?

17:47.000 --> 17:48.206
- It was Leo.

17:48.275 --> 17:50.827
- No one forced you to,
Donnie!

17:50.896 --> 17:52.724
Ugh, what's that smell?

17:52.793 --> 17:54.931
- I love you
this much.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.413
- No, no, you don't.
I'm your least favorite!

17:57.482 --> 17:58.862
- Uh, Leo's infected.

17:58.931 --> 18:00.413
Quarantine him.

18:02.310 --> 18:04.931
- Hey, you need me to get
to the Must Say Yes stage.

18:05.000 --> 18:06.103
We need to ask
for the onesies--

18:06.172 --> 18:08.517
Whoa, it is really hot.

18:08.586 --> 18:09.482
Is there a fire?

18:09.551 --> 18:10.655
There's a fire here, right?

18:10.724 --> 18:11.793
The floor is made of lava?

18:11.862 --> 18:13.034
[screams]

18:13.103 --> 18:14.862
- Down to three.

18:14.931 --> 18:16.724
All right, fellas,
let's be careful

18:16.793 --> 18:18.896
so the rest of us can make sure
we get what we want.

18:18.965 --> 18:20.379
Who's got eyes
on the package?

18:20.448 --> 18:21.344
- [gasps]

18:21.413 --> 18:22.896
I lost him.

18:22.965 --> 18:24.655
Oh!

18:28.724 --> 18:29.689
[both gasp]

18:29.758 --> 18:31.689
- Hot soup!

18:31.758 --> 18:34.379
- [yelps]

18:34.448 --> 18:35.413
all: Ah!

18:35.482 --> 18:36.482
- Oh!

18:36.551 --> 18:38.310
Where'd Splinter go?

18:38.379 --> 18:40.103
all: Huh?

18:40.172 --> 18:42.000
- Guys! I think I felt him!

18:42.068 --> 18:43.172
- Hey, that is my butt!

18:43.241 --> 18:47.068
[all grunting]

18:47.137 --> 18:49.482
Ow! Would everyone please
stop hitting me?

18:51.241 --> 18:52.862
- Now I've really got him.

18:52.931 --> 18:55.551
Take that, itchy fuzzball.

18:55.620 --> 18:58.103
- [groaning]

18:58.172 --> 19:00.103
- Oh, not my lab!

19:00.172 --> 19:03.172
[dramatic music]

19:03.241 --> 19:10.241
♪ ♪

19:14.068 --> 19:16.620
- Donnie, you hit?

19:16.689 --> 19:18.000
- No, no, I'm fine.

19:18.068 --> 19:19.655
I just cut myself
on that janky old door.

19:19.724 --> 19:21.103
Everything's okay.

19:21.172 --> 19:22.517
Raph, did you decide
what we're gonna ask for?

19:22.586 --> 19:25.103
- Yeah, I got it.
I'm gonna ask for--

19:25.172 --> 19:28.310
- [clears throat]
- Huh? What?

19:28.379 --> 19:31.689
- ♪ I'm... ♪

19:35.068 --> 19:38.310
- I can't feel my ears!
Nothing is worth this!

19:38.379 --> 19:41.068
- We're so close.
Only two stages left.

19:41.137 --> 19:43.724
- And three
totally healthy turtles left.

19:43.793 --> 19:46.275
Man, why is it so hot in here?

19:49.517 --> 19:52.827
Oh, you're gonna get squat
from Splinter without Donnie,

19:52.896 --> 19:54.965
not without ol' Donnie!

19:55.034 --> 19:57.689
I'm the brains
behind this operation!

19:57.758 --> 19:58.827
[sneezes]

19:58.896 --> 20:01.172
- Uh, what stage
are we on now?

20:03.620 --> 20:05.206
- Okay, okay, okay.
Listen, listen, listen.

20:05.275 --> 20:07.034
Okay, we open on noodle shop.

20:07.103 --> 20:09.379
It's raining.

20:09.448 --> 20:13.137
Lou Jitsu--
hot soups, two assassins,

20:13.206 --> 20:16.103
then wham--
interdimensional doorway opens,

20:16.172 --> 20:18.206
and out walks...
♪ Dun-dun-duh ♪

20:18.275 --> 20:21.551
Jupiter Jim,
and we smash to titles!

20:21.620 --> 20:23.206
- This is amazing.
Keep going.

20:23.275 --> 20:24.689
- We're almost
at stage seven.

20:24.758 --> 20:28.620
This is the closest I've been
to success, uh, ever.

20:28.689 --> 20:31.448
- [sneezes]

20:32.275 --> 20:33.413
We're done.

20:33.482 --> 20:35.517
Raph is totally
gonna blow this.

20:35.586 --> 20:39.551
He has no idea what to ask for,
which means--

20:39.620 --> 20:41.241
Getting hot.

20:41.310 --> 20:43.620
It's like I'm on the sun here.

20:43.689 --> 20:45.689
- [chuckles]

20:45.758 --> 20:47.206
I'm not gonna blow this.

20:47.275 --> 20:49.724
- Raphael, I love you,
my brother,

20:49.793 --> 20:52.310
but you do tend to fail
in big moments.

20:52.379 --> 20:55.724
Pishposh.
But that's what makes you you.

20:55.793 --> 20:57.241
Now bring it in, buddy.

20:57.310 --> 21:00.586
I'm gonna hug you
till a smile comes out.

21:00.655 --> 21:01.896
- Enough!

21:01.965 --> 21:03.827
Raph's got this,
'cause in big-time moments,

21:03.896 --> 21:07.793
leaders make big-time shots,
and I'm big-time!

21:07.862 --> 21:09.000
- [hissing] He must say yes.

21:09.068 --> 21:11.034
Make him say yes.

21:11.103 --> 21:12.103
- Enough!

21:12.172 --> 21:13.103
Don't mess this up, Raph.

21:13.172 --> 21:14.137
Don't mess this up.

21:14.206 --> 21:15.931
- Don't forget we only get

21:16.000 --> 21:19.275
to ask for one thing,
my little Raph-a-doodle.

21:19.344 --> 21:21.689
- I know exactly
what I'm asking for.

21:26.620 --> 21:29.758
[dramatic music]

21:29.827 --> 21:32.241
- [moans and sniffles]

21:32.310 --> 21:34.896
♪ ♪

21:34.965 --> 21:36.586
- Master Splinter,

21:36.655 --> 21:39.137
I know you'll say yes
to whatever I ask for.

21:39.206 --> 21:41.068
I want you to give--

21:41.137 --> 21:44.655
- Raph-a-doodle a hug!

21:44.724 --> 21:46.931
Everybody loves hugs!

21:47.000 --> 21:49.137
- What? No!
Anything but that!

21:49.206 --> 21:51.517
- [laughing]
Come here!

21:51.586 --> 21:52.517
- Oh! Ow!

21:52.586 --> 21:53.965
- [smooching]

21:54.034 --> 21:55.241
- [sneezes]

21:55.310 --> 21:57.103
- Ooh, flu.

21:57.172 --> 22:00.103
Papa wants a new bike.

22:00.172 --> 22:01.448
[bicycle bell dings]

22:03.344 --> 22:05.275
[sneezes]

22:05.344 --> 22:09.344
Uh-oh.
